@node "PGuide" "IOT - The Player's Guide"


  Insignia Of Terror is a new type of RPG.. After years of development it
 is a formidable multiplayer game that offers something to new and
 experienced Roleplayers alike. A completely open ended game, IOT lets
 players choose their own goals, friends and enemies, and has a very
 detailed campaign world.

  This player's guide to IOT tells you everything you need to know before
 you can start playing in the game, including masses of background
 information for the gameworld, and graphic illustration!

  The player's guide is FREE, and available in AmigaGuide and HTML formats
 with a printed version to follow shortly. The files can be found on BBSs
 worldwide through aminet, or downloaded from Aminet itself. The Sword &
 Skull BBS is guarenteed to carry ALL Arcane Lore related files, call on:
 0113 2260866 (UK).


@endnode

@node "MMag" "Mystic Magazine"


  Mystic Magazine is an AmigaGuide/HTML quarterly diskmag primarily for
 discussion of MFD products, and what has been happening in the land of
 Irall Rhin, where IOT is set. The magazine is edited by Mike Dawes, the
 author of IOT, who also contributes most to the magazine's text.
 Readers are encouraged to send in contributions of any type (as long as
 it's legal!) For inclusion in the diskmag. Mmag is an indisposable source
 of background information for IOT, especially if as a player you don't
 have access to ALNet or the S&S BBS.

  Issue 1 of Mystic Magazine can be found in all the normal places, and
 the possibility of a printed version is currently being looked into.

  Mystic magazine is FREE in it's electronic forms.


@endnode

@node "GMG" "Mystic RPG, the GM's guide"

 
  This is the definative Mystic RPG rulebook, containing all the
 information from the players guide, and much, much more. The guide
 explains all of the tests and tables, details character generation,
 combat, magic calculation etc, as well as having a HUGE section full of
 background info, and creature statistics.. In fact, it documents over 70
 indevidual races! Also there are pages deticated to the realm of Irall
 Rhin, it's cities, and how it's politics work. The guide also contains
 the information you need to start playing a Mystic based game at home
 with your friends, as well as how to run a Mystic RPG in ANY setting,
 from medieval, through modern day to fantasy and futuristic! The
 information's also there for you to start GMing IOT alongside MFD, so as
 a GM you'd effectively own a town in Irall Rhin, GMing many players.

  The GM's Guide is available ONLY in printed form. This is to increase
 it's usefulness as well as decrease the chances of piracy.

  The Guide's cost has not yet been decided.


@endnode

@node "GMTool" "GM's tool pack"


  This package contains utilities designed by MFD and other contributers.
 All of the utils in this archive are for the AMIGA range of computers,
 and have been designed to help the GM do his/her job. Utils include a
 character generator that can read initiation sheets and output perfect
 Ascii character sheets, an Arexx dice rolling module for GED and WW6, a
 description adder for use in players turns, a helpful 'wizard in a
 window' who can help you with any of the rules, and a turn interpretter
 that can respond to the *Command lines.

  It is possible that any part of the archive mentioned above may not be
 included, especially in it's first release.

  The price for the GM's tool pack is undecided at this stage, but money
 will be divided between the authors of the included programs.


@endnode

